Type: Package
Package: validateHOT
Title: validateHOT - Package to Validate Holdout Tasks in Conjoint
    Analysis & MaxDiff
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Joshua", "Schramm", , "schramm94@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5602-4632")),
    person("Marcel", "Lichters", , "test@123.com", role = "ctb")
  )
Description: validateHOT is a package that validates validation/holdout
    tasks (HOTs) in (adaptive) Conjoint analysis as well as MaxDiff. You
    define the validation/holdout task and afterwards, choose different
    validation metrics. validateHOT is a user-friendly tool to help you
    test the predictive validity of your data. validateHOT currently only
    works for hierarichal bayes raw data estimated with Sawtooth Software.
